article.headline: Illinois St. 68, Indiana St. 53
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Levi Dyer scored 18 points to lead Illinois State to a 68-53 victory over Indiana State on Wednesday. Dyer scored 11 of his points in the second half as the Redbirds (13-14, 5-11 Missouri Valley Conference) shot 15-of-24 (63 percent) from the floor in the second period. Greg Dilligard and Anthony Slack each added 12 points for Illinois State. Cole Holmstrom and Adam Arnold both scored 11 points to lead the Sycamores (12-14, 5-11) in their 10th loss of the last 11 games. Indiana State led 8-3 on Trent Wurtz's layup with 16:31 left in the first half, but the Redbirds took the lead for good when Osiris Eldridge hit a jumper with 12:18 remaining in the half. Illinois State outrebounded the Sycamores 33-22 and outscored them in the paint 34-18.
